Package: forestvalues
Title: Comprehensive Forest Economics Toolkit
Version: 2.0.0
Authors@R:
    person("Ryan", "Smith", , "rsmith@sevenislands.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A comprehensive toolkit for forest economic analysis including
    net present value (NPV), internal rate of return (IRR), land expectation
    value (LEV/Faustmann), optimal rotation age, stumpage valuation, income
    projection, Monte Carlo simulation, sensitivity analysis, timberland
    appraisal (income, liquidation, and sales comparison approaches), and
    U.S. timber taxation (IRC Section 631, cost depletion, Section 194
    reforestation incentives). Includes formatted Excel export with live
    formulas. Designed for both practitioners and researchers in forest
    economics and natural resource management. All methods are documented
    with academic citations and example datasets.
License: not for commercial or non-academic uses.
Encoding: UTF-8
